                        <summary>
                            
                            <p>On the west base of the Varadarāja Perumāḷ shrine in the Chandramauḷīśvara temple.</p>						
                            
                            <p>Kulōttuṅga I. Year 41 : 1110-11 A.D.</p>						
                            
                            <p>This inscription records the gift of 3 sheep for a <hi rend="italic">sandhi</hi> lamp for god Tiruvakkarai Ālvār by a shepherd (<hi rend="italic">maṉṟāḍi</hi>) Śelvan Vaḍugan.</p>						
                            
